00:22:43,680 --> 00:22:49,080
good Protestants that the devil finds work for idle hands to do.

240
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:53,840
But the basic principle of the whole thing has been completely overlooked that the purpose

241
00:22:53,840 --> 00:23:00,680
of the machine is to make drudgery unnecessary.

242
00:23:00,680 --> 00:23:08,240
And if we don't allow it to achieve its purpose we live in a constant state of self-frustration.

243
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:16,920
So then if a given manufacturer automates his plant and dismisses his labor force and

244
00:23:16,920 --> 00:23:26,600
they have to operate on a very much diminished income, say some sort of dole, the manufacturer

245
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:34,120
suddenly finds that the public does not have the wherewithal to buy his products.

246
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:43,320
And therefore he has invested in this expensive automotive machinery to no purpose.

247
00:23:43,320 --> 00:23:49,640
And therefore obviously the public has to be provided with the means of purchasing what

248
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:52,520
the machines produce.

249
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:54,600
People say that's not fair.

250
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:56,280
Where's the money going to come from?

251
00:23:56,280 --> 00:23:58,000
Who's going to pay for it?

252
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:00,680
The answer is the machine.

253
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:09,040
The machine pays for it because the machine works for the manufacturer and for the community.

254
00:24:09,040 --> 00:24:17,560
This is not saying, you see, that this is not the statist communist idea that you expropriate

