00:24:55,520 --> 00:24:58,240
of a minimum income.

263
00:24:58,240 --> 00:25:01,800
Now you see that absolutely horrifies most people.

264
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:06,160
Say all these waste drawers, these people who are out of a job because they're really

265
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:14,080
lazy, see, given the money, yeah.

266
00:25:14,080 --> 00:25:18,320
Because otherwise the machines can't work.

267
00:25:18,320 --> 00:25:20,560
We come to blockage.

268
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:26,400
This was the situation of the Great Depression when here we were still in a material sense

269
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:33,320
a very rich country with plenty of fields and farms and mines and factories, everything

270
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:40,920
going but suddenly because of a psychological hang-up, because of a mysterious mumbo-jumbo

271
00:25:40,920 --> 00:25:45,440
about the economy, about the banking.

272
00:25:45,440 --> 00:25:52,960
We were all miserable and poor, starving in the midst of plenty, just because of a psychological

273
00:25:52,960 --> 00:25:53,960
hang-up.

274
00:25:53,960 --> 00:26:01,080
And that hang-up is that money is real and that people ought to suffer in order to get

