00:26:01,080 --> 00:26:02,080
it.

276
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:07,480
But the whole point of the machine is to relieve you of that suffering, which is an ingenuity.

277
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:15,880
You see, we are psychologically back in the 17th century and technically in the 20th.

278
00:26:15,880 --> 00:26:19,920
And here comes the problem.

279
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:31,560
So what we have to find out how to do is to change the psychological attitude to money

280
00:26:31,560 --> 00:26:39,360
and to wealth and furthermore to pleasure and furthermore to the nature of work.

281
00:26:39,360 --> 00:26:41,920
And this is a formidable problem.

282
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:48,760
It requires the best brains in public relations, in propaganda, in all that kind of thing, in

283
00:26:48,760 --> 00:26:57,520
all the media, television, radio, newspapers, everything to try to get across a message

284
00:26:57,520 --> 00:27:01,040
to the vast general public about what money is.

285
00:27:01,040 --> 00:27:04,080
You see, the difficulty is this.

286
00:27:04,080 --> 00:27:09,120
When the public suspects that the money that is being issued, the dollar bills being issued

287
00:27:09,120 --> 00:27:16,160
by the government, are only paper and stand only for paper, they start putting up prices.

288
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:20,640
So you get an inflationary situation where the more paper money there is, the higher

289
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:24,640
and higher and higher the prices go.

290
00:27:24,640 --> 00:27:32,240
Which is a very stupid psychological maneuver.

291
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:35,880
And people have to be persuaded.

292
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:40,240
The least effective way of persuading people is passing laws, but they have to be persuaded

